Former Nigeria Football Federation Secretary General and Osun State Football Association Chairman, Chief Taiwo Ogunjobi is dead, National Daily learnt.
The sad news which was posted on on WhatsApp groups on Monday morning by his Personal Assistant, Tunde Shamsudeen shocked all football followers, stakeholders and fans who described Taiwo as a good leader.
According to a source close him, he was last seen in the public last Wednesday when he came to Oshogbo Township stadium to watch week 7 NPFL match between Remo Stars and MFM FC.
His absence at the 2019 Osun state Sports Award on Sunday (yesterday) raised the question from people of Osun.
